Erste Drops Second Day After Moody’s Downgrades Hungarian Unit

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-04-05T08:42:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/erste-drops-second-day-after-moody-s-downgrades-hungarian-unit.html
Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)  retreated for a
second day in Prague and Vienna trading.  The stock fell 0.9 percent to 872.7 koruna as of 10:08 a.m.
in Prague. In Vienna, where the company has its headquarters,
Erste retreated 0.5 percent to 35.535 euros.  Erste’s local unit was among seven Hungarian banks that had
their credit ratings downgraded today at Moody’s Investors
Service, which cited risks from foreign-currency loans and
shrinking profits. Austrian banks will need 15 billion euros to
18 billion euros ($21 billion to $26 billion) in additional
capital by 2019 to comply with Basel III rules, central bank
Governor Ewald Nowotny told Wirtschaftsblatt newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  